title: Bayside NEW album shudder at 320kbs
description:
The new album from Bayside at 320 kbs! 



Shudder is the fourth full length album from the band Bayside.[1] Anthony Raneri described the album as having a more punk sound than their previous record The Walking Wounded.

On September 5th, 2008, the album was leaked onto various file-sharing sites, and its first single "No One Understands" has caused massive buzz from fans through the band's MySpace page. The band also played "I Think I'll Be OK" at shows during the summer as a preview for fans.

As of September 22nd, the album was put up to stream on the band's official Myspace page. Also, as of October 4th, the music video for the song "No One Understands" was posted for viewing on the band's official MySpace page.
